NOTE ON THIRD-PARTY ASSETS

The MIT license above covers ONLY the configuration files, scripts, and Rust
code authored in this repository. It does NOT cover third-party components,
which keep their own upstream licenses:

Fetched at install time (not redistributed here):
  * Chicago95 (icons, cursors, sounds, GTK theme) -- GPL-3.0
        https://github.com/grassmunk/Chicago95
  * Win2k icon theme (KDE-Store item 1120706)     -- see the item's page

Bundled / vendored in this repository:
  * Droid Sans  (rust/mde-ui/fonts/)              -- Apache-2.0
        the Tahoma stand-in, embedded in the binary
  * HardInfo2   (vendor/hardinfo2, git submodule) -- GPL-2.0-or-later
        https://github.com/hardinfo2/hardinfo2
        the platform's Device Manager; built and launched as a separate
        program (mere aggregation), not linked into the MIT-licensed code.
